<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/24511:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-01T22:00:00-04:00">October 1,
                                    1942—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>242. Your 308, September 25, 5 p.m. For McBride. Department approves of
                            exchange of notes with wording proposed by you. It is believed, however,
                            that the word “and” should be substituted for “in” immediately after the
                            phrase “military use of airports”.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>